{
  "doc_id": "49849",
  "text": "As a consequence, there is great interest for cryptographic researchers to design pairing-free identity-based cryptographic schemes [CITATION_1] . The first non-pairing IBMS scheme was proposed in [CITATION_2] with three-round interactive communications and under R. Rivest, A. Shamir, L. Adleman (RSA) assumptions. Later, a communication efficiency-improved IBMS scheme under RSA assumptions was presented in [CITATION_3] with two-round interactive communications. Yang et al. [CITATION_4] proposed an efficient improved IBMS scheme that aims to save the computational resources and communication bandwidth. Even if the RSA assumption approaches the integer factorization assumptions, unfortunately, the RSA assumption has not yet been proved equal to the factorization assumption (denoted as Problem 3).",
